"56:73:5" : {s: 56, a: 73, w: 5, r: "قوي", t: "لِّلْمُقْوِينَ", l: "مُقْوِين", lc: 1, tl: "lil'muq'wīna", lb: "নির্জন মরুবাসী",e: "for the wayfarers in the desert", b: "মরুবাসীদের জন্য", i: "bagi orang-orang yang musafir", f: 1, rm: "to be, become strong, prevail, be able to do, be powerful, be vigorous, be forceful. quwwatun (pl. quwan) - power, strength, vigour, resolution, firmness, determination. qawun - desert. aqwa - to stay in desert. muqwin - dwellers of desert/wilderness (it is derived from the verb qawiya which means: it became desolate or deserted).", ag: "لام الجر وال التعريف وأسم فاعل", eg: "Preposition lām and Determiner al and Noun Active participle", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACT_PCPL", qual: "GEN", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "قَوِىٌّ"},
